        {
          "anchor" : "Polar-Coordinates",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Polar Coordinates",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In polar coordinates, a point is represented by the ordered pair [r, θ]. Note the square brackets, to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "distinguish from the Cartesian coordinates (x, y).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "These forms can be converted to each other using the following equations:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r = +\\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}",
            "\\tan(\\theta) = \\frac{y}{x}",
            "",
            "x = r \\cos(\\theta)",
            "y = r \\sin(\\theta)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The angle θ is measured anticlockwise from the positive x-axis, typically in radians. The distance r is",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the distance from the origin to the point and is positive.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note that the fact that ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\tan(\\theta) = y\/x$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " does NOT mean that ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\theta = \\tan^{-1}(y\/x)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This is because the tangent function is periodic, and this would make it seem like theta only",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "lies in the 1st and 4th quadrants (to the right of the y-axis).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The line from (x, y) to the origin will make an angle of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\tan^{-1}(y\/x)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " with the x-axis, but",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "it may not be accurate to which ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "direction",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the line the point is. For example, the point (-1, 1)",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "is in the 2nd quadrant (top-left), but ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\tan^{-1}(1\/-1)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is in the 4th quadrant (bottom-right).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We use polar coordinates because some problems are easier to solve in polar coordinates than in Cartesian",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "coordinates, especially circles - its literally just ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$r=a$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for a circle with radius ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$a$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Finding-Polar-Coordinate-Forms",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Finding Polar Coordinate Forms",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Circle-Example",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Circle Example",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To find the polar coordinate form of a circle:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "x^2 + y^2 = 1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We then substitute ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$x$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$y$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " with their polar equivalents:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "(r \\cos(\\theta))^2 + (r \\sin(\\theta))^2 = 1",
            "r^2 (\\cos^2(\\theta) + \\sin^2(\\theta)) = 1",
            "r^2 = 1"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Which makes sense because its a circle with radius 1.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Parabola-Example",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Parabola Example",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To find the polar coordinate form of a parabola:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "y=2x^2"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Note: This is an upwards parabola, not a sideways one. ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$a$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " here is ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$1\/8$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", not ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$1\/2$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We substitute and get:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r \\sin(\\theta) = 2(r \\cos(\\theta)^2)^2",
            "r \\sin(\\theta) - 2r^2\\cos(\\theta)^2 = 0",
            "r(\\sin(\\theta) - 2r\\cos(\\theta)^2) = 0"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Either ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$r = 0$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", which is obviously false as that would be a point, not a parabola, or:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\sin(\\theta) - 2r\\cos(\\theta)^2 = 0",
            "2r\\cos(\\theta)^2 = -\\sin(\\theta)",
            "r = \\frac{1}{2} \\tan(\\theta) \\sec(\\theta)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A slightly more complicated example is:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "y^2 = 1 + 2x"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Unlike the previous example, this does not start at the origin. Substituting gives:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "(r \\sin(\\theta))^2 = 1 + 2(r \\cos(\\theta))",
            "r^2 \\sin^2(\\theta) - 2r \\cos(\\theta) - 1 =",
            "r^2 \\sin^2(\\theta) + r(-2\\cos(\\theta)) - 1 = 0"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We can then use the quadratic formula to solve for r: (we only consider the positive root, as the parabola is on the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "positive side of the y-axis)",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r = \\frac{2\\cos(\\theta) + \\sqrt{(-2\\cos(\\theta))^2 - 4(\\sin^2(\\theta))(-1)}}{2\\sin^2(\\theta)}",
            "",
            "= \\frac{2\\cos(\\theta) + \\sqrt{4\\cos^2(\\theta) + 4\\sin^2(\\theta)}}{2\\sin^2(\\theta)}",
            "",
            "= \\frac{2\\cos(\\theta) + 2}{{2\\sin^2(\\theta)}}",
            "",
            "= \\frac{\\cos(\\theta) + 1}{\\sin^2(\\theta)}",
            "",
            "= \\frac{\\cos(\\theta) + 1}{1 - \\cos^2(\\theta)}",
            "",
            "= \\frac{\\cos(\\theta) + 1}{(1 - \\cos(\\theta))(1 + \\cos(\\theta))}",
            "",
            "= \\frac{1}{1 - \\cos(\\theta)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Line-Example",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Line Example",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For a line which passes through the origin, we can use the polar form:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "y = mx",
            "\\theta = \\tan^{-1}(m)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "But for a line which does not pass through the origin, it is a bit more complicated:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "y = mx + c",
            "r \\sin(\\theta) = m(r \\cos(\\theta)) + c",
            "r \\sin(\\theta) - mr \\cos(\\theta) = c",
            "r(\\sin(\\theta) - m \\cos(\\theta)) = c",
            "r = \\frac{c}{\\sin(\\theta) - m \\cos(\\theta)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Finding-Cartesian-Forms",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Finding Cartesian Forms",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example,",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r = \\cos(\\theta)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We can multiply both sides by r to get:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r^2 = r \\cos(\\theta)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Notice that ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$r \\cos(\\theta) = x$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". We can then substitute:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r^2 = x",
            "sqrt(x^2 + y^2)^2 = x",
            "x^2 + y^2 = x",
            "x^2 - x + y^2 = 0"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Completing the square gives:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "(x - \\frac{1}{2})^2 - (\\frac{1}{2})^2 + y^2 = 0",
            "(x - \\frac{1}{2})^2 + y^2 = (\\frac{1}{2})^2 = \\frac{1}{4}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "So we get a circle with center ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$(1\/2, 0)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and radius ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$1\/2$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Generic-Conics-with-Polar-Coordinates",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Generic Conics with Polar Coordinates",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A conic is defined as the set of points on a plane such that the ratio of the distance from a point to a focus and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the distance from the point to a directrix is the eccentricity ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$e$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " of the conic. That is:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\frac{\\textrm{distance from point to focus}}{\\textrm{perpendicular distance from point to directrix}} = e"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In particular, if",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$e<1$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", it is an ellipse",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$e=1$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", it is a parabola",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$e>1$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", it is a hyperbola",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "Graph_Conic Section Polar Derivation",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We can derive the polar form of a conic from this definition:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\frac{\\textrm{distance from point to focus}}{\\textrm{perpendicular distance from point to directrix}} = e",
            "",
            "\\frac{r}{d+r\\cos(\\theta)} = e",
            "",
            "r = e(d + r\\cos(\\theta))"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Solving for r gives:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r = ed + re\\cos(\\theta)",
            "r - re\\cos(\\theta) = ed",
            "r(1 - e\\cos(\\theta)) = ed",
            "r = \\frac{ed}{1 - e\\cos(\\theta)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "By definition, one of the foci is at the origin. Note that the foci will be horizontal, since",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\cos(y)$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is the same for a point P and its reflection across the y-axis.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Inspecting-the-Conic",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Inspecting the Conic",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "We know that when ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$e = 0$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", the conic is a circle. You can see this from the polar form:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r = \\frac{0}{1 - 0\\cos(\\theta)} = 0"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This is a point at the origin, which is a circle with radius 0.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$0 < e < 1$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", the conic is an ellipse. Inspecting the polar form:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "r = \\frac{ed}{1 - e\\cos(\\theta)}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In this case, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$1 - e\\cos(\\theta) > 0$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " since ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$e\\cos(\\theta) < 1$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
